<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id83ffe6a0-3a70-11f1-ab1a-a784e0a454e2" identifier="/us/usc/t41/s8707"><num value="8707">§ 8707.</num><heading> Criminal penalties</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A person that knowingly and willfully engages in conduct prohibited by <ref href="/us/usc/t41/s8702">section 8702 of this title</ref> shall be fined under title 18, imprisoned for not more than 10 years, or both.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id83ffe6a1-3a70-11f1-ab1a-a784e0a454e2">(<ref href="/us/pl/111/350/s3">Pub. L. 111–350, § 3</ref>, <date date="2011-01-04">Jan. 4, 2011</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/124/3841">124 Stat. 3841</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
